250 g Ground Turkey
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
6 g Montreal Spice Blend
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 unit(s) Lettuce
2 tbsp Ketchup
½ tbsp Dijon Mustard
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
2.5 g Italian Herb Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
1 unit(s) Tomato
1 tsp Sugar*
⅓ tsp Salt*
0.15 tsp Pepper*
3 tbsp Oil*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Cut cucumber into 1/2-inch rounds.
Cut tomatoes into 1/2-in slices.
Remove and discard outer layer and stem of lettuce. Halve lengthwise, then chop into 1/2-inch pieces.
Drain pickles and reserve juice.
Roughly chop pickles.

To a large bowl, add Dijon, 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar, vinegar, half the Italian Herb Spice Blend (use all for 4 servings) and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. (NOTE: This is your dressing.)
To a small bowl, add mayo, half the reserved pickle juice and ketchup. Stir to combine.
Pre-heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.

When the pan (from step 2) is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, turkey and Montreal Spice Blend.
Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Reduce heat to low, then add cheese and pickles. Cover and cook for 1-2 min, until cheese is melted.

Meanwhile, halve buns.
Arrange buns on an unlined baking sheet, cut-sides up. Drizzle with 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Toast in the middle of the oven for 5-6 min, until golden. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns, so they don't burn.)

To the bowl with dressing (from step 2), add lettuce and cucumber. Season with pepper, then toss to combine.
Spread ketchup-mayo mixture on both sides of the buns.
Stack turkey mixture and tomatoes on bottom buns. Close with top buns. Cut in half, if you like.
Divide salad between plates.